    "summary": "Hello! \nMy name is Marc, a studious and energetic team player. In groups, I am a flexible and patient guy with good communicative skills. I love to work together with people from different cultures, because it gives a different and insightful challenge and enables me to reflect upon my own culture. This is one of the reasons I have lived in Kenya for 3 months, and in Colombia for 6 months. To reflect further upon culture, work and myself, I started studying philosophy. \n\nI've always been quite curious, which has led me to study physics (focus on low-carbon power production), philosophy (focus on moral phenomenology), work in banking (focus on sustainable development), and learn different languages. I hope to continue on this path - currently through a PhD in physics.\n\nWhile working towards a goal, I am focused and use creative ways to achieve it. A personal goal is to grasp the world in all of its aspects.",
